caption: Stopped at curbside right in front, put on my covid mask and ran in to see if they had a breakfast sandwich - sausage egg and cheese. They did, and I was able to pay contactless right at the entrance counter. Waited in the car and had my sandwich 10 min later. Really excellent, with cheese and egg sticking out the sides ... perfect!

I thought I was still waiting for my food and then they brought something with eggs. It also looked like something like cheese on top of the vegan bowl, so I still have to see what's actually in it. I ordered the Hungry Man's Special to go (“had to” be at work). Atmosphere was cool, “old school” yet updated. I would have loved to sit and chat with the friendly hostess and nice nurses having breakfast at the counter, also an eighties music mix was audible but not overwhelming. They have a few taps and I noticed Narragansett tall boys, to the uninitiated a light and refreshing lager, the beer the captain drank in Jaws. It would have complimented my breakfast nicely, I’ll have to swing by again.
Great Place

This place still exists because there is a lack of options nearby. Food is bland and overpriced. I went twice. We had breakfast burrito, spinach omelet, and the last straw was the carnitas chilaqules, where even the egg on top tasted bland (no salt).

Filthy nasty.  Bad overpriced food.  I was offered 3 *filthy* knives (as in smeared and filmy oily) before the exasperated server told me to sort through the bin to claim one for myself.  With my barehands, the same bin that he was giving utensils to other customers out of.  I left and called the health department.  If they can't clean the silverware, how nasty are the dishes? They also hide their health Dept rating.

Came in from out of town and had the best Breakfast! Best Diner in Cambridge for sure!
This is the best diner in Cambridge! Came in from out of town and crushed a huge breakfast! Prices were spot on as well!

I am disappointed to even have to be writing this about my experience last week at the Mass Ave. Diner since I’ve been a true fan for about 15 years now, and this was my go-to spot! My first issue is the fact that the online menu, which should be taken down, was actually pretty deceptive when I learned upon arrival it no longer existed. So there goes the Hungry Man’s Special, $8.99, that I eagerly anticipated. Second issue, I spent $13.99 to recreate the hungry man special, and the woman at the front desk (not sweet Karolina) told me that people have chewed her out about this issue. Which she was appreciating that I didn’t get upset, or rude. Third issue, the chef is mean mugging me in the background as if I’m taking too long to order. My fourth issue is after repeating a couple of times that I wanted cheese on my scrambled eggs, and being assured that my order was taken down, I did not receive cheese on my eggs, but I’ll tell you what I did receive; an extremely skimp breakfast which literally was scraps! Scraps of broken pieces of bacon which amounted to 1 piece, the end part of toast (you know, the part that we all throw away), MAYBE 4 small pieces of fried potatoes, and the side order of french toast was also stale (this is not an exaggeration) with syrup that if you threw to a wall, would not drip, in other words it was super old!  You ever get the feeling that someone just didn’t feel like making your food that day? Or like you were specifically targeted for whatever reason (again, I was so pleasant to the lady at the front desk, I promise!) Well, this was it.  This drastic increase on price for less? Really sad!
Super easy value
I love that restaurant, especial Roxanna. She's very cain person, professional, intelligent and very friendly.

Solid food at great prices! My omelette was delicious and my dad got a full sized breakfast sandwich for just over $4. Great music too!

Very bizarre experience. We came in 1.5 hours before closing, and the owner/manager (?) seemed very angry to see us. He was very brusque, made us move to a different table for seemingly no reason (because the whole place was empty), and was generally inattentive (also racist??). Everything on the menu had hidden fees i.e. condiments, meat options, vegetable options -- so what seemed like a fairly priced meal was actually overpriced. The manager also told one person who came in right after us that the place was closed, even though they were supposed to be open for another hour, at least.

Good prices and portions only problem we had was a member of our party ordered hash and didn't get it until we were nearly done. Bars open all day too so feel free to kick back with a narragansett lager

Had breakfast here twice while visiting Boston. Food was great, portions were good, and reasonably priced. They were very accommodating to a friend's dairy allergy and kept checking up on us to make sure everything was good. Staff was very friendly and kind!! Highly recommend.

HUGE fan of this place. My best friend and I try to come at least once a week because it is the kind of place that just makes you want to be a regular. I have never once had to wait to be seated. Everyone who works there is so nice. The food is simple but delicious and very inexpensive. You can get a huge plate of eggs, bacon, hashbrowns and toast for 5 or 6 dollars. Also, as every diner should, they are quick about refilling coffee which is a major plus for me. If you are looking for a consistent and genuine diner, this is the place.
